<strong> <a href="http://www.collioure.com/" target="_blank" rel="external">Collioure</a></strong>";s:9:"post_name";s:19:"spain-mediterranean";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"2";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2016-05-03 09:45:01";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2016-04-21 15:18:09";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2016-04-21 15:18:09";}i:2;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"281";s:10:"post_title";s:15:"Black Mountains";s:12:"post_content";s:379:"If you want to cool down and see a totally different landscape, just drive north for 20 minutes and you will find yourself in the Black Mountains (La Montagne Noire). This beautiful mountain range is covered in tall pine forests, within which lie lakes (some with beaches) and trails, perfect for mountain biking, hiking, picnicing and walking under the cool canopy of the trees.";s:9:"post_name";s:15:"black-mountains";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"2";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2016-05-03 09:49:47";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2016-04-21 14:19:46";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2016-04-21 14:19:46";}i:3;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"282";s:10:"post_title";s:18:"Rennes le Ch√¢teau";s:12:"post_content";s:614:"For those who have enjoyed reading the Da Vinci Code or Holy Blood Holy Grail, you may be interested in visiting Rennes le Ch√¢teau, 40 minutes drive into the foothills of the Pyrenees mountains. Here stood the house of the priest B√©renger Sauni√®re who supposedly discovered the original blood line behind the Holy Grail. For a nominal fee, you can visit the house and the little chapel where the 'treasure' was found. There is a pretty gardern with a breath-taking view of the valley below.

<strong><a href="http://www.renneslechateau.com/" target="_blank" rel="external">www.renneslechateau.com</a></strong>";s:9:"post_name";s:17:"rennes-le-chateau";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"2";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2016-05-03 09:44:43";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2016-04-21 14:20:32";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2016-04-21 14:20:32";}i:4;O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"283";s:10:"post_title";s:13:"The Pyren√©es";s:12:"post_content";s:1518:"The Pyren√©es have everything to offer; kayaking, rafting, climbing, walking, mountain biking and in the winter months skiing, snowboarding and husky sleigh rides. There are countless amazing attractions to visit, such as the Labouiche underground river, which is a most unusual cruise: 60 m underground, comfortably seated in a boat, you will be taken along the underground river over a distance of nearly 1,5 km, from rooms to galleries decorated with a host of concretions and pools - a very cool thing to do on a very hot day!

There are many beautiful places to visit including the Cathar Castles and Abbeys. Lastours is a must, four castle ruins perched on the edge of cragy rocks, dating back to the 11th Century. Other castles include Montsegur, Qu√©ribus and Peyrepertuse, each has magnificent views over the valleys below and the mountains all around. All the castles have footpaths leading up that can be steep but still easily walkable.
